      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-3xl font-display text-4xl font-bold leading-tight grad-text md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
        How Answer Engine Optimisation Works
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-ink-200">
        <strong class="text-white">Answer engines do not rank pages — they run a four-stage pipeline that classifies the query, retrieves candidate sources, synthesises an answer, and selects citations.</strong> Understanding every stage of that pipeline is the prerequisite for optimising it. This guide maps each stage and explains precisely what content, structural, and entity signals determine whether your brand is selected as the answer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Two-column layout: TOC + article -->
  <div class="container-wide py-12 lg:grid lg:grid-cols-[220px_1fr] lg:gap-12">

    <!-- Sticky TOC -->
    <aside class="hidden lg:block">
      <div class="sticky top-24">
        <span class="eyebrow">On this page</span>
